# [MBONED](../wg/mboned.html)

## Summary

The MBONED Working Group session at IETF 126 focused on active working group documents, significant developments in browser-based multicast, and real-world deployment experiences. 

Key themes included:
* A transition to consecutive (rather than concurrent) Working Group Last Calls (WGLC) to improve participation and feedback quality.
* Active implementation efforts in browser-based multicast delivery utilizing Media over QUIC (MoQ) and WebTransport.
* Real-world deployment reports from major sporting events (US Open, Australian Open, Wimbledon) highlighting the necessity of IPv6 support.
* Innovations in end-to-end native multicast CDNs, including Dynamic Internet Multicast Tunnels (DIMT) and Chrome integration.
* A proposal to tunnel Automatic Multicast Tunneling (AMT) over QUIC to address packet loss, authentication, and discovery issues.

